Each comparison may be performed inside Fuller’s triangle. Criteria are numbered as serial numbers 1, 2,…, k. Users then work with the triangular diagram; the double lines formed by serial numbers are arranged in pairs so that each pair of criteria appears exactly once. The user indicates (by encirclement) which criterion is more important for comparing each pair. We mark the number of encirclements of i-th criterion as n
